Final Thoughts
You just built something that would cost you $24,000/year from Bloomberg, or $50-100/month from portfolio apps, or weeks of developer time if you hired someone. Total cost: a modest AI subscription and a couple hours of your time.

But the real value is not the report. It is that you now know how to use an AI coding agent. This same skill works for building reports, automating data analysis, creating dashboards, processing documents, and a thousand other things.

Once you get comfortable with AI coding agents, you will start seeing opportunities everywhere. "Wait, the AI could automate this boring task." "The AI could build a tool for that." It fundamentally changes how you think about problems.

Remember: AI is not a magic wand. You will hit bugs. Things will break. The AI will occasionally misunderstand you. But the iteration cycle is so fast that it does not matter. Just tell the AI what went wrong and it fixes it. That is the game. And it is a fun game.

